THE GAME
--------

  'Xix' (pronounced 'KSIX') is a Workbench game where the goal is
to 'connect' 3, and only 3, shapes together. Also, any series of
connected shapes must include at least one 'X' shape. If there are
2 'X' shapes in any series and/or if all shapes in that series are
of the same colour, the better it is...

  Gameplay is done by rotating shapes (except 'X' shapes, as these
cannot move) so they connect diagonally. One important thing to
remember is that the 'center' shape in a series must only be
connected to two shapes, one connection for each connected shape,
and the 'peripheral' shapes must only be connected to the center
shape. When a series of 3 connected shapes is made, the shapes are
then removed from the game board and are replaced by new coloured
shapes.

  The game ends when there are no remaining 'X' shapes on the
board.

  Have fun!

